To design and develop a Movie Showcase website using HTML that displays movie details such as movie name, genre, director, poster, and description, allowing users to easily explore different movies. 
Procedure – Movie Showcase Website Step 1: Creating the Basic HTML Structure 
The project was started by creating an HTML file using the <!DOCTYPE HTML> declaration along with <html>, <head>, and <body> tags to define the basic structure of the webpage. 
 
Step 2: Setting Website Title 
Inside the <head> section, the title “Movie Showcase” was added using the <title> tag to identify the webpage in the browser 
 
Step 3: Designing the Home Page 
The main page was designed with:
•	Website title displayed using <h1>
•	A short introduction using <p> 
•	Horizontal line <hr> for section separation 
 
Step 4: Displaying Movie Details 
Each movie section was created using:
•	<h2> tag for movie title
•	<img> tag to display the movie poster
•	<p> tag to show genre, director, and description 
 
Step 5: Adding Multiple Movie Sections 
Multiple movies were displayed by repeating the same structure for each movieand separating them using the <hr> tag for clarity. 
 
Step 6: Final Testing 
The webpage was tested in a web browser to ensure:
•	Proper display of movie details
•	Correct loading of images
•	Clean and readable layout 
 
Working 
•	The browser reads the HTML file and displays the content.
•	The <head> section sets the webpage title.
•	The <body> section displays movie details.
•	Headings highlight movie names.
•	Images visually represent movie posters.
•	Paragraphs describe movie information.
•	Horizontal lines separate each movie section for better readability. 
